description._content: Catalog #: 09_01596 Title: Elwyn H. Gibbon Special Collection Photo Additional Information: Portrait of Elwyn Gibbon in military uniform. Handwritten inscription ""Just before I left the army - note the worried look. Taken at March Field - October 1933. Weight - 140 lb. Note the 31st Bomb Squadron insignia"", Elwyn Gibbon (b.1911 d.1942) was an American pilot who served as a pilot in the Chinese Air Force in the Foreign Volunteer Squadron. Later he served as a Vultee Aircraft Company test pilot in Karachi, India, where he died in a plane crash in 1942. Tags: Elwyn H.
